<section class="w-section">
  <div class="w-inner">
    <p class="w-eyebrow reveal">Agent-Native</p>
    <h2 class="w-h2 reveal" data-stagger="2">Natively built for AI&nbsp;agents.</h2>
    <p class="w-lead reveal" data-stagger="3">Hand your agent an API key. It calls <code>as_tools()</code> to discover every available method, pulls market and weather context in a single call, and backtests strategies against point-in-time snapshots. You define the goal. The agent figures out how to get&nbsp;there.</p>

    <div class="w-pillar-grid">
      <div class="w-pillar reveal">
        <h3>60% fewer tokens</h3>
        <p>TOON encodes tabular data at 40-60% fewer tokens than JSON. One year of daily settlement pairs fits in 24K tokens and passes straight into the model&nbsp;context.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="w-pillar reveal" data-stagger="2">
        <h3>One line to tool-use</h3>
        <p><code>client.as_tools()</code> returns Anthropic-compatible tool definitions for every SDK method. Drop them into <code>messages.create(tools=...)</code> and your agent&nbsp;self-orients.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="w-pillar reveal">
        <h3>No look-ahead bias</h3>
        <p>Every query accepts an <code>as_of</code> parameter. <code>snapshot(as_of=...)</code> returns exactly what was knowable at that UTC instant. Climate records stay withheld until the publication threshold&nbsp;passes.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="w-pillar reveal" data-stagger="2">
        <h3>Replay any backtest</h3>
        <p>Every response carries a <code>data_version</code> hash that pins the exact data state. Tag your training runs with it and replay any backtest exactly as it looked at decision&nbsp;time.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
